Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP 
(4 TBSP for 4 servings). Halve, core, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1} into strips.

Toss sliced onion and poblano on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of 
@olive oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} 
(you'll add more to the sheet then).

While veggies roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all 
over with @fajita spice blend{1}, salt, and pepper. Drizzle with olive oil and rub 
to evenly coat.

Once veggies have roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully add 
chicken to empty side. Return to top rack until chicken is browned and cooked through 
and veggies are tender and slightly crisp, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> If veggies are done before chicken, remove from sheet and continue roasting chicken.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}; let rest at least ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, dice @Roma tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, minced onion, and a squeeze of lime juice. 
Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, 
~{30%seconds}. Divide between plates.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Serve chicken, veggies, pico de gallo, @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp}, remaining lime 
wedges, and @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} in separate bowls or plates for a 
build-your-own fajita bar!